.TH abtranslate 1 "2005-02-17"
.SH NAME
abtranslate \- Al Bhed translator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B abtranslate [options] text
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B abtranslate 
is an Al Bhed translator.  It translates from English to Al Bhed, Al Bhed to English, and Al Bhed to phonetics.  Al Bhed is a fictional cipher from the game Final Fantasy X.  There is also a GUI frotend for abtranslate called gBhed.
.SH OPTIONS
Command Line Options
.TP
.B -e, --english
Translate from English to Albhed.
.TP
.B -a, --albhed
Translate from Al Bhed to English.
.TP
.B -p,  --phonetics
Translate from Phonetics to Al Bhed.
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display help and exit.
.TP
.B -version, --version,
Display version information.
.TP
.B --author
Display author information
.TP
.B --license
Display license information
.SH EXAMPLES
Example usage:
.TP
.B abtranslate -e Hello world!
.TP
If no text is specified upon the command line, abtranslate \
will read from stdin untill EOF is encountered (usually sent \
with ctrl-d)
.SH FILES
.P
\fI@prefix@/bin/abtranslate
